</uri>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF9704BBFC1BFE90559B" blockId="22.[163,778,909,1023]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBFC1BFE8555C7" box="[163,283,910,931]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Third maxilliped ischium smooth, lacking vertical sulcus; epibranchial tooth small, pointed; postfrontal crest distinct, completely traversing carapace.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF9704BBFBBDFDAA52DC" blockId="22.[163,779,1064,1208]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBFBBDFEBF5259" box="[163,289,1064,1085]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970535FBBDFE28525A" authority="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels, 2022" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" box="[301,438,1064,1086]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="TRIBE NOV." tribe="Erimetopini">Erimetopini</taxonomicName>
is derived from a combination of the English words 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970585FBD2FE7B5238" box="[413,485,1095,1116]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
and West, as a reference to the range of this tribe that includes an area that encompasses the 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970568FB11FE2652FD" box="[368,440,1156,1177]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
Basin and all of West Africa (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF9704B3FB37FF6252DC" box="[171,252,1186,1208]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="17.[145,224,1267,1289]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetId="figure-288@17.[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 8. Maps showing the distributional ranges of (A) Potamonautinae, (B) Maritimonautini, (C) Erimetopini and (D) Potamonautini." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461497/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). The gender is masculine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF9704BBFB77FDF25293" blockId="22.[163,620,1249,1271]" box="[163,620,1249,1271]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBFB77FEB95293" box="[163,295,1250,1271]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<typeStatus id="2D53885B4F3BFF9704BBFB77FF465293" box="[163,216,1250,1271]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Type</typeStatus>
genus:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF97052BFB77FDFB5292" authority="Rathbun, 1894" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" box="[307,613,1249,1271]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF97052BFB77FE285293" box="[307,438,1250,1271]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF9705A5FB74FDFB5292" author="Rathbun MJ" box="[445,613,1249,1271]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="25 - 27" refId="ref36341" refString="Rathbun MJ. 1894. Descriptions of a new genus and two new species of African fresh-water crabs. Proceedings of the U. S. National Museum 17: 25 - 27." type="journal article" year="1894">Rathbun, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF9704BBFAB5FDFC5317" blockId="22.[163,780,1312,1395]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBFAB5FDB15352" box="[163,559,1312,1334]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">G e n e r a i n c l u d e d: E r i m e t o p u s</emphasis>
R a t h b u n, 1 8 9 4, 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9704BBFAAAFD915330" authority="(Bott, 1955)" baseAuthorityName="Bott" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[163,527,1342,1364]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Longipotamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBFAAAFE1D5330" box="[163,387,1343,1364]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Longipotamonautes</emphasis>
