</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF9704BBFA09FE7950C3" blockId="22.[163,780,1436,1703]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBFA09FED953D5" box="[163,327,1436,1457]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Distribution:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF97054EFA09FE7153D6" authority="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels, 2022" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" box="[342,495,1436,1458]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="TRIBE NOV." tribe="Erimetopini">Erimetopini</taxonomicName>
is found in West and Central Africa in the following countries: 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF97069EFA2EFC9553B4" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1894" box="[646,779,1467,1488]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Erimetopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF97069EFA2EFC9553B4" box="[646,779,1467,1488]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Erimetopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970557FA4CFDFC538A" box="[335,610,1497,1519]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
and the D.R. 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF9704BBFA6DFF745069" box="[163,234,1528,1549]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF9704E0FA6DFED65069" box="[248,328,1528,1550]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="18.[163,241,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-252@18.[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 9. Maps showing the distributional ranges of the four genera of Erimetopini (A) Erimetopus, (B) Longipotamonautes, (C) Nesonautes and (D) Occidensonautes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461499/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF970545FA6DFDA35069" baseAuthorityName="Bott" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[349,573,1528,1549]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Longipotamonautes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF970545FA6DFDA35069" box="[349,573,1528,1549]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Longipotamonautes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF9706B7FA6DFC99506A" box="[687,775,1528,1550]" name="Nigeria" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF9704BBF982FEBB5048" box="[163,293,1559,1580]" name="Cameroon" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
, the D.R. 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF9705B4F982FE625048" box="[428,508,1559,1580]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Congo</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970659F983FE95502F" name="Central African Republic" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF97050FF9A0FEFD502F" box="[279,355,1589,1611]" name="Gabon" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Gabon</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF9705D4F9A0FD50502E" box="[460,718,1589,1611]" name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF9706C7F9A0FF5C500D" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="18.[163,241,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-252@18.[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 9. Maps showing the distributional ranges of the four genera of Erimetopini (A) Erimetopus, (B) Longipotamonautes, (C) Nesonautes and (D) Occidensonautes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461499/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9704C2F9C1FEC1500D" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" box="[218,351,1620,1641]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Nesonautes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704C2F9C1FEC1500D" box="[218,351,1620,1641]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Nesonautes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970613F9C1FD50500E" box="[523,718,1620,1642]" name="Sao Tome Island" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">São Tomé Island</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF9706C7F9C1FF5C50EC" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="18.[163,241,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-252@18.[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 9. Maps showing the distributional ranges of the four genera of Erimetopini (A) Erimetopus, (B) Longipotamonautes, (C) Nesonautes and (D) Occidensonautes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461499/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF97051CF9E7FE5F50E3" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" box="[260,449,1650,1671]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" genus="Occidensonautes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF97051CF9E7FE5F50E3" box="[260,449,1650,1671]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Occidensonautes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in West Africa from 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF9704BBF904FF6350C3" box="[163,253,1681,1703]" name="Senegal" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Senegal</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F3BFF970538F904FEE850C3" box="[288,374,1681,1703]" name="Nigeria" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF97059DF904FE4650C2" box="[389,472,1681,1703]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="18.[163,241,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-252@18.[243,1363,195,1255]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 9. Maps showing the distributional ranges of the four genera of Erimetopini (A) Erimetopus, (B) Longipotamonautes, (C) Nesonautes and (D) Occidensonautes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461499/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F3BFF9704BBF945FBB2577C" blockId="22.[163,780,1744,1888]" lastBlockId="22.[827,1443,197,280]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9704BBF945FE8C5081" box="[163,274,1744,1765]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Remarks:</emphasis>
Each of the four genera in this tribe has been recovered as a well-supported lineage in the clade for 
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F3BFF9704D2F898FECA5147" authority="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels, 2022" authorityName="Cumberlidge &amp; Daniels" authorityYear="2022" box="[202,340,1805,1827]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" status="TRIBE NOV." tribe="Erimetopini">Erimetopini</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF97057BF898FE2D5146" box="[355,435,1805,1827]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[163,244,905,927]" captionTargetBox="[164,1447,197,865]" captionTargetId="figure-453@2.[163,1449,195,866]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. A, maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna based on four DNA loci with support values (posterior probabilities and bootstrap values of the ML analyses) with a geological timescale below the tree topology. Posterior probabilities&gt; 0.95 pP (*above branch) and bootstrap values&gt; 75% (* below branch) were regarded as statistically supported and are shown on the tree topology. Clade A, Liberonautinae, clade B, Potamonautinae, clade B1, Maritimonautini, clade B2, Erimetopini, clade B3, Potamonautini. B, detail of the maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna showing Clade B3 Potamonautini with the species included in the five genera within the tribe: Arcopotamonautes (B3[1]), Lirrangopotamonautes (B3[2]), Platythelphusa (B3[3]), Potamonautes s.s. (B3[4]) and Rotundopotamonautes (B3[5])." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461481/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF9705ABF898FE5D5146" box="[435,451,1805,1826]" captionStart="Figure" captionStartId="11.[145,172,844,866]" captionTargetBox="[149,757,195,804]" captionTargetId="figure-779@11.[149,757,195,804]" captionText="Figure 2. Liberonautinae. Gonopods 1 and 2 of Liberonautes latidactylus, NMU9.V.2005B (CW 72, CL 47.2, CH 20.5, FW 19.3 mm) Guinea, West Africa. A, left G1 ventral view; (B) left G1 dorsal view; (C) left G2 ventral view. Scale bar: A, B = 2.8 mm, C = 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461483/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">2</figureCitation>
) and these relationships are also supported by other recent molecular studies of these taxa (
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF970533F8DFFDAF5104" author="Daniels SR &amp; Klaus S" box="[299,561,1866,1888]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="119 - 128" refId="ref33119" refString="Daniels SR, Klaus S. 2018. Divergent evolutionary origins and biogeographic histories of two freshwater crabs (Brachyura: Potamonautes) on the West African conveyer belt islands of Sao Tome and Principe. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 127: 119 - 128." type="journal article" year="2018">Daniels &amp; Klaus, 2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1; 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F3BFF97069DF8DFFCEA56BE" author="Wood LE &amp; De Grave S &amp; Cumberlidge N &amp; Kennerley A &amp; Daniels SR" box="[645,884,197,1888]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290" pagination="2219 - 2230" refId="ref37030" refString="Wood LE, De Grave S, Cumberlidge N, Kennerley A, Daniels SR. 2019. A phylogenetic perspective on biodiversity patterns of Afrotropical freshwater crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Potamonautidae). Aquatic Conservation: Marine and Freshwater Ecosystems 29: 2219 - 2230." type="journal article" year="2019">
Wood 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F3BFF9706D3F8DEFC9B513B" box="[715,773,1866,1888]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">et al.</emphasis>
, 2019
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1). The genera can be distinguished from each other by differences in the G1 TA (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F3BFF97011AFF71FAEF569D" box="[1282,1393,228,250]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="14.[163,241,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,195,1303]" captionTargetId="figure-309@14.[163,1443,195,1303]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 4. Gonopods 1 and 2 of the four genera in Erimetopini. A–C, Erimetopus vandenbrandeni; D–F, Longipotamonautes ballayi; G–I, Nesonautes margaritarius; J–L, Occidensonautes ecorssei. Scale bar: A–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461487" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461487/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="1290">Fig. 4A–L</figureCitation>
; see key to genera above).
</paragraph>
